                           αj Var(vj )      αj Var(âj )      αj\n\n                                                      14\n\fThe second-order condition is −αj Var(vj ) < 0, so the criterion is strictly concave whenever\nVar(vj ) > 0. Imposing the contract-space constraint ρj ∈ [0, 1] projects the interior maximizer onto\nthe feasible interval, yielding ρ∗j = clip(Ij /αj , [0, 1]).\nFor the Gaussian special case, âj = a∗j +ξj with ξj independent of a∗j gives Ij = SNRj /(1+SNRj ),\nso the interior benchmark rate is ρ∗j = SNRj /[αj (1 + SNRj )].\n\nB.2    Proof of Proposition 1\n\nProof of Proposition 1. For the attribution-aligned benchmark, the reduced criterion as a function of\nρj is\n                                         αj\nShell cwd was reset to /inspire/qb-ilm/project/video-generation/chenxie-25019/hyr/iHateTheWorld555.github.io", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "e9af5140-6217-4988-8d6b-64e94e7289f8", "uuid": "40183103-39c1-4bca-b72c-0d39616090c8", "timestamp": "2026-07-06T10:07:38.865Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "                                                                          royalty                                                                         D-TRAK wins 8\n                      =2                                                                                      D-TRAK\n\n\n\n\n                                         creators (of 22)\n\n\n\n\n                                                                                                                                 D-TRAK surplus\n            0.75                                                                                      75                                          10 7\n\n\n\n\n                                                                                      % gap closed\n                     EKFAC royalty                          20\noptimal *   0.50     D-TRAK                                                               